s of the pastry sheets. Brush the remaining exposed pastry with butter, then carefully roll pastry into a large sausage shape to encase the filling. Coil the pastry into a round snail shape, brushing with additional butter as needed, then transfer to a flat baking tray lined with baking paper."},{"content":"Patch up any breaks in the pastry with small pieces of filo and butter."},{"content":"Bake for 30 - 40 minutes (200°C) or until pastry is golden and crispy. Cut into wedges and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve salmon filo spiral with a simple garden and herb salad."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 10m","6 portions"]}